li.p:
We can find a common denominator to write the sum of the two terms as one rational expression.

  \amp \frac{1}{x^{3}}+\frac{2-x^{5}}{1-x}
  \amp = \frac{1-x}{1-x} \cdot \frac{1}{x^{3}}+\frac{x^{3}}{x^{3}} \cdot \frac{2-x^{5}}{1-x}
  \amp = \frac{1-x}{(x-1)x^{3}}+\frac{x^{3}(2-x^{5})}{x^{3}(1-x)}
  \amp = \frac{1-x+2x^{3}-x^{8}}{x^{3}(1-x)}

